Flow discharge radar system
The flow discharge radar system comprises of two radars. The first radar
measures the velocity of the surface river flow and the second radar measures
the vertical height of the fixed radar from the river.
The river discharge or volume flow rate in m
3
/second is calculated from the
cross-sectional area of the river together with the river surface velocity and the
vertical height of the river surface from the radar.
The surface velocity measuring radar works on the doppler phenomenon
whereby an electromagnetic wave (EM) of 24 GHz is transmitted and reflected
from the flowing river. Due to doppler effect the reflected EM is at a slightly
different frequency which is proportional to the river velocity. The received
EM is compared with the transmitted EM and the river surface velocity is
calculated.

An illustration of river surface
velocity measurement setup from
side view, the observation area
(marked in yellow) depends on the
height of radar and the beam width
in elevation θel
The level radar works on 60 GHz and uses Frequency Modulated Continuous
Wave (FMCW) concept. It measures the height of the radar from the water
surface.
The combined radar system is able to calculate volume flow rate of the river or
can be used as an early warning flood radar. During a flood, first the surface
velocity of the river increases and then after a period of time the water level in
the river starts to rise. By having access to both the surface velocity and surface
level (vertical height) data, an early flood warning system can be devised.

Non Contact Surface Velocity Radar
Technical Data
Radar Analog Front End : InnosenT (Germany)
Radar Frequency : 24 GHz
Radar Radiated Power : 20 dBm (EIRP)
Radar Max. Height : 30 m
Radar Angle : 30 deg w.r.t. horizontol
Radar Opening Angle : 12 deg Azimuth
24 deg Elevation
Radar Signal processing PCB : STM32H750VBT6
Flow Measurement : 0 m/s .... 15 m/s
Flow Resolution : 0.001 m/s
Flow Accuracy : 2 %
Flow Measurement Time : 30 seconds
Power Supply : 9 to 30 VDC
Current Consumption : 150 mA (when active)
Material : Plastic / Metal Housing
Weight : 200 g
Dimensions : e.g. 100 x 100 x 60 mm
Housing : IP67
Environment : Unaffected by rain, fog,
smoke, dust or light
Temperature : -40 deg C ...... 85 deg C
Interfaces : RS485 MODBUS (standard)
UART, RS232, 3G/4G LTE
Protection : Overcurrent, Over Voltage,
Thunder & Lightining, ESD,
Reverse polarity
Radar Level Sensor
Technical Data

Radar Frequency : 57 ... 64 GHz
Radar Radiated Power : 12 dBm (EIRP)
Radar Angle : 4 deg
Radar Signal processing PCB : STM32H750VBT6
Level Measurement : 0.5 m ... 32.5 m
